        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-08-15T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-08-15T12:00:00-05:00" n="664" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d664">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00116 PW/8–1545: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-08-15T18:00:00+01:00">August 15, 1945—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received August 15—4:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>8280. From Hodgson. Lord Wright informed me Aug 15 that he will not propose to
                    put Emperor’s name on list. He said he would await US action. He expressed
                    similar views in respect preparing and adopting list of major Jap war criminals.
                    His assistant Oldham confirmed these views and said Lord Wright had been
                    misunderstood. [Hodgson.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Winant</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
